' ============================================================================
' C++ Development Workflow (Pre-Python Integration)
' ============================================================================
== C++ Development Workflow ==

note over Researcher, Executor
  **Use Case**: Iterative C++ kernel/executor development
  **Before** integrating with Python benchmarks
end note

Researcher -> Ionoc: ionoc bench --preset latency --full --lock-clocks
activate Ionoc

Ionoc -> GPUMgr: lock GPU clocks (admin elevation)
activate GPUMgr
note right: Reduce CV from 20% → 5-10%\nStable performance measurement
GPUMgr --> Ionoc: clocks locked
deactivate GPUMgr

Ionoc -> Executor: run C++ benchmark (5000 iterations)
activate Executor
Executor -> Executor: BatchExecutor\nor StreamingExecutor
Executor --> Ionoc: latency metrics
deactivate Executor

Ionoc -> GPUMgr: restore GPU clocks (auto-cleanup)
activate GPUMgr
GPUMgr --> Ionoc: clocks restored
deactivate GPUMgr

Ionoc --> Researcher: Performance Card\n✓ NO CHANGE / ⚠ REGRESSION
deactivate Ionoc

note right of Ionoc
  **ionoc Commands**:
  - ionoc bench (quick validation)
  - ionoc bench --preset <name> --full
  - ionoc profile nsys/ncu
  - ionoc bench --lock-clocks
end note

opt If profiling needed
  Researcher -> Ionoc: ionoc profile nsys --stats
  activate Ionoc
  Ionoc -> Nsight: nsys profile with config
  activate Nsight
  Nsight -> Executor: run with profiling
  activate Executor
  Executor --> Nsight: trace data
  deactivate Executor
  Nsight -> Artifacts: save .nsys-rep
  activate Artifacts
  deactivate Artifacts
  Nsight --> Ionoc: profiling complete
  deactivate Nsight
  Ionoc --> Researcher: artifacts/profiling/cpp_dev.nsys-rep
  deactivate Ionoc

  Researcher -> Researcher: nsys-ui (analyze timeline)
end

' ============================================================================
' Profiling Workflow (Python End-to-End)
' ============================================================================
== Production Profiling Workflow ==

note over Researcher, Nsight
  **Use Case**: Profile complete Python → C++ pipeline
  **After** C++ integration complete
end note

Researcher -> IProf: iprof nsys latency
activate IProf

IProf -> Hydra: auto-load profiling config (20 iter)
activate Hydra
Hydra --> IProf: ExecutorConfig + BenchmarkConfig
deactivate Hydra

opt With GPU clock locking
  IProf -> GPUMgr: lock GPU clocks
  activate GPUMgr
  GPUMgr --> IProf: clocks locked
  deactivate GPUMgr
end

IProf -> Bench: run_latency.py +benchmark=profiling
activate Bench
Bench -> Nsight: nsys profile wrapper
activate Nsight
Nsight -> Executor: run profiling workload
activate Executor
Executor --> Nsight: trace data
deactivate Executor
Nsight -> Artifacts: save .nsys-rep
activate Artifacts
deactivate Artifacts
Nsight --> Bench: profiling complete
deactivate Nsight
Bench --> IProf: benchmark complete
deactivate Bench

opt With GPU clock locking
  IProf -> GPUMgr: restore clocks
  activate GPUMgr
  GPUMgr --> IProf: clocks restored
  deactivate GPUMgr
end

IProf --> Researcher: artifacts/profiling/latency_<timestamp>.nsys-rep
deactivate IProf

note right of IProf
  **iprof Commands**:
  - iprof nsys latency/throughput/realtime/accuracy
  - iprof ncu latency (kernel analysis)
  - Auto-selects profiling vs full benchmark config
  - Supports Hydra overrides: engine.nfft=8192
end note

' ============================================================================
' Experiment Execution Phase
' ============================================================================
== Experiment Execution Phase ==

Researcher -> CLI: iono analysis
activate CLI
CLI -> Snake: snakemake --cores 4
activate Snake

Snake -> Snake: parse Snakefile
Snake -> Snake: build DAG

group Latency Sweep
    Snake -> Bench: run_latency.py --multirun
    activate Bench
    
    Bench -> Hydra: load config
    activate Hydra
    Hydra -> Hydra: compose configuration
    Hydra -> Hydra: setup multirun sweep
    Hydra --> Bench: config objects
    deactivate Hydra
    
    loop For each parameter combination
        Bench -> Executor: BatchExecutor/StreamingExecutor(config)
        activate Executor
        Executor -> Executor: initialize CUDA
        Executor -> Executor: allocate buffers
        Executor --> Bench: executor instance
        deactivate Executor

        Bench -> Executor: submit(test_data, output)
        activate Executor
        Executor -> Executor: GPU FFT processing
        Executor --> Bench: results + metrics
        deactivate Executor
        
        Bench -> MLflow: log_metrics()
        activate MLflow
        MLflow -> MLflow: store experiment
        deactivate MLflow
        
        Bench -> Artifacts: save CSV
        activate Artifacts
        Artifacts -> Artifacts: write latency_summary_*.csv
        deactivate Artifacts
    end
    
    Bench --> Snake: latency_sweep.done
    deactivate Bench
end

group Throughput Sweep
    Snake -> Bench: run_throughput.py --multirun +benchmark=throughput
    activate Bench
    note right: Similar process as latency\nwith different parameters\nGPU clock locking optional
    Bench -> Hydra: load config
    Bench -> Executor: benchmark loop
    Bench -> MLflow: log metrics
    Bench -> Artifacts: save CSV
    Bench --> Snake: throughput_sweep.done
    deactivate Bench
end

group Accuracy Sweep
    Snake -> Bench: run_accuracy.py --multirun +benchmark=accuracy
    activate Bench
    note right: Validates against\nreference implementation
    Bench -> Hydra: load config
    Bench -> Executor: benchmark loop
    Bench -> MLflow: log metrics
    Bench -> Artifacts: save CSV
    Bench --> Snake: accuracy_sweep.done
    deactivate Bench
end

Snake --> CLI: benchmarks complete
deactivate Snake
deactivate CLI

